        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "*from Namolovan Nicolae on the mailing list*\n\n{code}\nclass ServersTable extends Zend_Db_Table {\n\tprotected $_name = 'servers';\n}\n\n$dbIns = array(\n   'name'=>'sdf',\n   'os_ver'=>'2'\n);\n\n$table = new ServersTable();\n$id = $table->insert($dbIns);\n{code}\n\nI get the follow error: \"Fatal error:  Uncaught exception\n'PDOException' with message 'SQLSTATE[HY093]: Invalid parameter\nnumber: parameter was not defined' in\n..\\Zend\\Db\\Adapter\\Abstract.php:157\"\n\nThis is because placeholders underscores are removed (in\nDb\\Adapter\\Abstract.php:124)\n{code}\n        \/\/ build the statement\n        $sql = \"INSERT INTO $table \"\n             . '(' . implode(', ', $cols) . ') '\n             . 'VALUES (:' . str_replace(\"_\", \"\", implode(', :', $cols)) . ')';\n{code}\nThe result are:\n{code}\nINSERT INTO servers (name, os_ver) VALUES (:name, :osver)\n{code}\nMy $dbIns don't contain any \"osver\" key, only \"os_ver\". That's why I\nget the PDO exception..\n\nWhat is the solution to this problem ?"
        },
